{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πρόδρομ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> <b>running forward with headlong speed,</b> π. ἦλθον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 211 (Lyric poetry); φυγάδα πρόδρομον 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 108 (Lyric poetry), etc.\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; μόλε π. variant in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 296 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>running before, going in advance,</b> π. στρατιή [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.14; κήρυκας π. προπέμπειν [prev. author] 1.60; π. ἥκω 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Iphigenia Aulidensis” 424 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; frequently of horsemen <b>in advance of</b> an army, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 4.121, 122; π. τῶν ἄλλων ἥκειν [prev. author] 7.203, compare 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.22; λεὼς π. ἱππότας 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Septem contra Thebas” 80 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>mounted skirmishers,</b> οἱ π. <b>'guides',</b> a special corps in the [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD(?): Macedonius Epigrammaticus army, 2nd c.AD: Arrianus Historicus “Anabasis” 1.12.7, compare 1st c.BC: Diodorus Siculus Historicus 17.17; οἱ ἀμφὶ [τὸν ἵππαρχον] πρόδρομοι 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “de Equitum magistro” 1.25; at Athens, 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Ἀθηναίων Πολιτεία” 49.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also, of light ships, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.AD: Alciphro Epistolographus 1.11. \">Refs 4th c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__3</b></Level3> <i>metaphorically</i>, <b>precursor,</b> ἀστέρα.. ἀελίου π.[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Ion Lyric poetry 10; ἠπίαλος πυρετοῦ π. 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Fragmenta” 332 (_anapaest meter_); δείπνου π. ἄριστον 4th c.BC: Eubulus Comicus 75.13; π. τοῦ δοκοῦντος καλλίστου εἶναι 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Charmides” 154a, compare 3rd c.AD: Plotinus Philosophus 6.7.7. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__4</b></Level3> π. (i.e. οἶνος), see at {πρότροπος}. <br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> as <i>substantive</i>, πρόδρομοι, οἱ, <br /><Level3><b>__II.1</b></Level3> see above [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1.2. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>northerly winds, preceding the etesian winds,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 361b24, “Pr.” 941b7, 4th-3rd c.BC: Theophrastus Philosophus “de Ventis” 11. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <b>early figs,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “CP” 5.1.5f, compare 1st c.AD: Plinius Rerum Naturalium Scriptor “Historia Naturalis” 16.113. \">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G4274","accentedUnicode":"πρόδρομος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G4390","matchingForm":"προτρέχω","stepTransliteration":"protrechō","gloss":"to outrun","_zh_tw_Gloss":"往前跑, 跑","_es_Gloss":"correr más rápido que","_zh_Gloss":"往前跑, 跑"}],"shortDef":"going before, forerunner","mediumDef":"going before, forerunner <br /><b>a precursor, forerunner, one who advances to explore and prepare the way,</b> <ref='Heb.6.20'>Heb. 6:20</ref>*","stepGloss":"forerunner","stepTransliteration":"prodromos","count":1,"_es_Definition":"precursor, heraldo","_zh_tw_Definition":"先行(字意為\"跑\"), 走在前面的 (來 6:20)","_zh_Definition":"先行(字意为\"跑\"), 走在前面的 (来 6:20)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"kẻ tiên phong; người báo trước. Xem G4390","_zh_tw_Gloss":"作先鋒","_es_Gloss":"precursor","_zh_Gloss":"作先锋"}]}